an class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#Ring\">Ring</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\">A</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Hom/Defs.html#RingHom\">→+*</a> <span class=\"fn\">B</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hf</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Function.html#Function.Surjective\">Function.Surjective</a> <span class=\"fn\">⇑<span class=\"fn\">f</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">{</a> <span class=\"fn\">g</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">:</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Hom/Defs.html#RingHom\">→+*</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">//</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Maps.html#RingHom.ker\">ker</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Maps.html#RingHom.ker\">ker</a> <span class=\"fn\">g</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">}</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Equiv/Defs.html#Equiv\">≃</a> (<span class=\"fn\">B</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Hom/Defs.html#RingHom\">→+*</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span>)</div></div>","info":{"doc":"A non-computable version of `RingHom.liftOfRightInverse` for when no computable right\ninverse is available, that uses `Function.surjInv`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Maps.html#RingHom.liftOfSurjective","kind":"def","line":1161,"name":"RingHom.liftOfSurjective","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Maps.lean#L1161-L1166"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Maps.html#RingHom.liftOfRightInverse\"><span class=\"name\">RingHom</span>.<span class=\"name\">liftOfRightInverse</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">A</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">B</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">C</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#Ring\">Ring</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#Ring\">Ring</a> <span class=\"fn\">B</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#Ring\">Ring</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\">A</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Hom/Defs.html#RingHom\">→+*</a> <span class=\"fn\">B</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f_inv</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">B</span> → <span class=\"fn\">A</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hf</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Function.html#Function.RightInverse\">Function.RightInverse</a> <span class=\"fn\">f_inv</span> <span class=\"fn\">⇑<span class=\"fn\">f</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">{</a> <span class=\"fn\">g</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">:</a> <span class=\"fn\">A</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Hom/Defs.html#RingHom\">→+*</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">//</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Maps.html#RingHom.ker\">ker</a> <span class=\"fn\">f</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Maps.html#RingHom.ker\">ker</a> <span class=\"fn\">g</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Subtype\">}</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Logic/Equiv/Defs.html#Equiv\">≃</a> (<span class=\"fn\">B</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Hom/Defs.html#RingHom\">→+*</a> <span class=\"fn\">C</span>)</div></div>","info":{"doc":"`liftOfRightInverse f hf g hg` is the unique ring homomorphism `φ`\n\n* such that `φ.comp f = g` (`RingHom.liftOfRightInverse_comp`),\n* where `f : A →+* B` has a right_inverse `f_inv` (`hf`),\n* and `g : B →+* C` satisfies `hg : f.ker ≤ g.ker`.\n\nSee `RingHom.eq_liftOfRightInverse` for the uniqueness lemma.\n\n```\n   A .\n   |  \\\n f |   \\ g\n   |    \\\n   v     \\⌟\n   B ----> C\n      ∃!φ\n```\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Maps.html#RingHom.liftOfRightInverse","kind":"def","line":1132,"name":"RingHom.liftOfRightInverse","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Maps.lean#L1132-L1159"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Maps.html#RingHom.liftOfRightInverseAux_comp_apply\"><span class=\"name\">RingHom</span>.<span class=\"name\">liftOfRightInverseAux_comp_apply</sp